Date: Tue, 26 May 2026 12:53:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] patch 0897: Tier 1 to 10 + US slot reservation + new
 Turnaround BUY-ZONE tier

User asked three things in the original request that I missed
focusing on the BLISSGVS / Movers fix:

  1. Expand Tier 1 from 8 to 10 stocks
  2. Make sure best USA names are included (not buried by India-heavy
     uploads)
  3. Create a NEW Tier 1 style section for turnaround setups

All three shipped:

(1) Tier 1 cap raised 8 to 10. TIER1_CAP / TIER1_US_MIN constants
    documented in code. Description string updated to reflect new cap.

(2) US slot reservation: after building the strict cross-confirmed
    list, count US-market names in tier1. If less than 2 AND qualified
    US names exist, drop the lowest-scoring non-cross-confirmed entry
    to make room and push the top US picks in. Never drops a star
    cross-confirmed entry.

(3) New turnaroundTier1 list: reads mb_turnaround_scored_v1
    localStorage, filters for archetype=TURNAROUND + isBestCandidate
    OR totalScore at least 60, sorts by totalScore, takes top 5.
    Each row gets a turnaround-specific thesis (phase + stage +
    survival), risk (top killers from playbook), horizon (2-4 quarters
    if phase 2/3 else 4-8), trigger (BUY-ZONE or concall).
    Renders as a new DecisionTierBlock labeled "TURNAROUND BUY-ZONE"
    with amber colour, immediately under the main IMMEDIATE ACTION
    block. Description makes it clear this is a different playbook -
    inflection setups, not sustained-quality compounders.

Type bookkeeping: added turnaroundTier1?: TierAction[] to HomeState
and extended the Pick<HomeState, ...> return type of buildSyncState.
tsc clean.
